Housing Development Said to Sell 12 Billion Rupees of Notes

-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 
2011-10-11T12:09:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/hdfc-said-to-sell-12-billion-rupees-of-91-day-commercial-paper.html
Housing Development Finance Corp. (HDFC) ,
 India ’s largest mortgage lender, raised 12 billion rupees ($243
million) selling 91-day commercial paper, said a person with
direct knowledge of the matter.  The Mumbai-based lender sold the notes to yield 9.5
percent, the person said, declining to be identified before an
announcement.  V. Srinivasa Rangan, executive director at HDFC, wasn’t
available to answer queries in two calls made to his office
telephone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anurag Joshi in Mumbai at 
 ajoshi53@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
